      "content": "It's not uncommon for a sudden, intense headache to be caused by dehydration, especially when you're consuming too much caffeine. Your body's way of telling you it needs more water, and a good night's sleep should help alleviate the symptoms. In the meantime, try drinking some water, maybe a glass of juice or a protein shake to help replenish your electrolytes. If the headache persists, you can also try taking an ibuprofen or acetaminophen, but be sure to follow the recommended dosage.",
